The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Saturday, May 22, 2004 				 Bus-auto crash in Basu yard
 A STAFF REPORTER																								A private bus ran head-on into an autorickshaw in front of Salt Lakes Indira Bhavan, residence of former chief minister Jyoti Basu, on Friday afternoon. 																								Two persons died and two others, including an 11-year-old, were injured. All of them were in the auto. 																								Police identified the dead as auto-driver Uttam Das (28) and Sudipto Das (39) and the injured as Bappa Biswas (11) and Ashish Das (52). Unconfirmed reports said another person was injured in the mishap. 																								Bappa was admitted to Bidhannagar State General Hospital but later shifted to NRS Medical College and Hospital as his head injury is stated to be serious. 																								Police said the bus was on its way to Karunamoyee and the auto towards Ultadanga. The driver of the bus was at fault, an official said. He was driving rashly.																								Uttam was a resident of Sri Krishna Colony, in Ultadanga, and he was taking Bappa  his nephew and a student of Class III  for a ride. Sudipto lived at Balarambati, in Hooghlys Singur. He was in Salt Lake on business, police said. 																								Witnesses said Sukanta Paul (36) was also injured. He was taken to a local nursing home and later shifted to NRS. Police did not corroborate. The driver fled with the bus.
